Anesthesiologists hailed as special heroes in fight against coronavirus But the most valuable procedure they perform also puts them in the most danger.
“The most critically ill COVID-19 patients suffer from acute respiratory distress syndrome [ARDS], a complex inflammatory response that causes the lungs to fill with fluid,” Dr. Odugbesan explains.
Dr. Odugbesan explains that the mortality rate for COVID-19 patients who require intubation remains as high as 65-85%.
“Members of our group have an extensive routine for donning and doffing PPE that often involves two people,” explains Dr. Odugbesan.
